+# Git Connection Fix - GitHub HTTPS Issue
+
+## Problem
+```
+fatal: unable to access 'https://github.com/Stranger-Siv/Kaam247.git/': 
+Failed to connect to github.com port 443 after 83 ms: Couldn't connect to server
+```
+
+## Diagnosis
+- ✅ GitHub is reachable via ping (network connectivity OK)
+- ❌ HTTPS port 443 connection fails (likely firewall/proxy/SSL issue)
+
+## Solutions
+
+### Solution 1: Use SSH Instead of HTTPS (Recommended)
+
+**Step 1: Check if you have SSH keys**
+```bash
+ls -la ~/.ssh/id_*.pub
+```
+
+**Step 2: Generate SSH key if needed**
+```bash
+ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
+```
+
+**Step 3: Add SSH key to GitHub**
+```bash
+cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
+# Copy output and add to GitHub: Settings > SSH and GPG keys > New SSH key
+```
+
+**Step 4: Change remote URL to SSH**
+```bash
+cd /Users/siv/Kaam247
+git remote set-url origin git@github.com:Stranger-Siv/Kaam247.git
+git push
+```
+
+### Solution 2: Fix HTTPS Connection
+
+**Option A: Check Proxy Settings**
+```bash
+# Check if proxy is set
+git config --global --get http.proxy
+git config --global --get https.proxy
+
+# If proxy is set incorrectly, unset it:
+git config --global --unset http.proxy
+git config --global --unset https.proxy
+```
+
+**Option B: Use GitHub CLI**
+```bash
+# Install GitHub CLI if not installed
+brew install gh
+
+# Authenticate
+gh auth login
+
+# Then try push again
+git push
+```
+
+**Option C: Increase Git Timeout**
+```bash
+git config --global http.timeout 300
+git config --global http.postBuffer 524288000
+```
+
+**Option D: Use Different Port**
+```bash
+# Try using port 443 explicitly
+git config --global url."https://github.com:443/".insteadOf "https://github.com/"
+```
+
+### Solution 3: Check Network/Firewall
+
+1. **Check if you're on VPN** - Try disconnecting VPN
+2. **Check firewall settings** - Allow Git/HTTPS connections
+3. **Try different network** - Mobile hotspot, different WiFi
+4. **Check corporate proxy** - If on corporate network, configure proxy
+
+### Solution 4: Use GitHub Desktop
+
+If command line fails:
+1. Install GitHub Desktop
+2. Open repository
+3. Push via GUI
+
+## Quick Test Commands
+
+```bash
+# Test HTTPS connection
+curl -I https://github.com
+
+# Test SSH connection
+ssh -T git@github.com
+
+# Test Git connection
+git ls-remote https://github.com/Stranger-Siv/Kaam247.git
+```
+
+## Current Status
+
+- **Branch**: main
+- **Commits ahead**: 1 commit ready to push
+- **Working tree**: Clean
+- **Remote**: git@github.com:Stranger-Siv/Kaam247.git (SSH)
+- **Issue**: Both port 22 and 443 are blocked (network/firewall issue)
+
+## Immediate Solutions
+
